Date: Sat, 14 Apr 2001 18:28:34 +0200
From: Martin Haditsch, MD, PhD <martin.haditsch@travel-clinic.at>

Control of Rabies by Canine and Wild-life Vaccination in Austria
----------------------------------------------------------------
A far as I know there was no rabies case neither in domestic animals nor in
wild-life in Austria for more than 2 years: an effect of vaccination,
using the oral vaccine to prevent infection in foxes and other wild-life.
Those looking up the map of registered cases in Europe will find that
Austria is a white spot surrounded by countries (mainly north, east and
south) with plenty of cases (animals crossing the borders been vaccinated as
well?).
Supporting poorer countries by providing Raboral could save many
lives - having an immunized (dog) community could be better than killing
them having the same problem repeatedly after a few months.
--
Martin Haditsch, MD, PhD
<martin.haditsch@travel-clinic.at>
